# Scenario Amend Marker

**Spec**: unable-cards-on-empty-inventory
**Baseline HEAD**: 43aef473d17a8e95241744bfe1eb000e0a41d0c3
**Amender**: pablo+claude
**Amend date**: 2026-05-08

## Reason

Customer-feedback-driven redesign of `UnableCategoryCard.vue`. The 2026-05-05 spec
explicitly captured the legacy visual style (subtle "no disponible" red pill, image
opacity 40%, accordion with long description, `bg-red-100 text-red-600` badge) and
declared visual restyling out of scope. Customers reported that this visual was not
clear enough — they did not realize the card represented an unavailable category and
attempted to interact with it as if it were available.

The user (project owner) approved a redesign on 2026-05-08 in plan mode. The new card:
- Replaces the small red pill with a top banner (`bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500`)
  that includes an icon and the unavailability reason composed from the search context
  (date range + pickup branch).
- Increases visual disengagement of the model image (grayscale + opacity 50%).
- Removes the accordion with `descripcion_larga` (it generated desire toward something
  the user could not buy).
- Adds two actionable CTAs ("Probar otras fechas", "Cambiar sucursal") that scroll the
  page to the `<div id="searcher" />` anchor.

## Scenarios affected

- **SCEN-U1**: behavioral assertions (count of unable cards, no toast, store invariants)
  unchanged. Only the DOM evidence selectors are updated to reflect the new card
  structure (the legacy `getByRole('heading', level: 3).filter(hasText: 'no disponible')`
  selector no longer matches because "No disponible" now lives in a banner div, not in
  an h3 heading; the h3 now contains `descripcion_corta`).
- **SCEN-U2**: same as SCEN-U1. Behavior unchanged, evidence selectors updated.
- **SCEN-U3**: full rewrite. Replaces:
  - "accordion + carousel respond" → "carousel responds; CTAs scroll to searcher"
  - `bg-red-100 text-red-600` pill → `bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500` banner
  - `img { opacity: 0.4 }` → `img { opacity: 0.5; filter: grayscale }`
  - `.contenedor-descripcion-carro { opacity: 0.7 }` → `{ opacity: 0.9 }`
  - "no descendants matching :text('Solicitar') / '$'" → preserved
  - Adds: top banner with `i-lucide-alert-triangle` icon, banner text from
    `useUnavailabilityContext().bannerText` (composable in logic layer), two
    `<UButton>` CTAs that on click invoke `document.getElementById('searcher')
    ?.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth'})`.
- **SCEN-U4**: unchanged. Mix-mode is about counts, not card visual.

## Non-goals update

The original "Visual restyling of UnableCategoryCard ... is not in scope" line is
replaced. It reflected the 2026-05-05 minimum-intervention scope; the 2026-05-08
amendment intentionally expands scope on customer-feedback grounds.

## Verification (post-amend)

- Logic suite: 197/197 (includes 9 new tests for `useUnavailabilityContext`).
- alquilatucarro suite: 159/159 (includes 7 new source-string tests for `UnableCategoryCard.vue`).
- alquilame suite: 33/33. alquicarros suite: 33/33.
- `UnableCategoryCard.vue` byte-identical across the 3 brands (verified with `diff`).
- Typecheck delta: −3 errors per brand (no new errors introduced; dead vars removed).
- Visual QA: captured with /agent-browser + LLNRAG009 mock (later reverted) on
  alquilatucarro local dev. Banner, dimming, both CTAs, and scroll-to-searcher all
  observed working. Screenshots stored at `/tmp/qa-unable-mocked.png`,
  `/tmp/qa-unable-full-card.png`, `/tmp/qa-after-cta-scroll.png`.

## Anti-reward-hacking note

The post-amend SCEN-U3 was written from the new design's spec (banner + 2 CTAs +
grayscale), then 7 source-string tests were written FROM that scenario. The component
was implemented to satisfy those tests. The scenario evolved because the user's intent
evolved (customer feedback), NOT because the code drifted from the original scenario.
The original 2026-05-05 spec is preserved in git history.
